The name we use in Aerospace industry is FPI (Flourescent Penetrant 
Inspection).  It is basically this messy neon green stuff you apply to 
the part, let it penetrate then wash and dry.  After drying, you 
inspect part under a black light.  Any cracks will glow under black 
light.

David

